Black work
The analysis of the labour market in Sinaloa is even more serious when considering the high proportion of undeclared work. According to INEGI, this includes 60.38 per cent of those employed in the country who work without paying into social security funds.
Unemployment and undeclared work are the lowest in the whole of Mexico, according to the statistics of the Instituto Mexicano del Seguro Social (Mexican Social Insurance Institution) and the Secretaría del Trabajo y Previsión Social (Government of Labour and Social Welfare in Mexico).
